<TITLE> Thousands pay homage to Manik at Shahid Minar </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, February 04 (bdnews24.com)The body of former communist leader and Gano Forum general secretary Saifuddin Ahmed Manik lay at the Central Shahid Minar Monday. People from all walks of life including politicians, educationists and intellectuals paid homage to the veteran politician before a last namaaz-e-janazaa at the national Eidgah following zohr prayers. Manik will be laid to rest at Mirpur Martyred Intellectuals' graveyard in the afternoon. At around 11:20 am Manik's coffin, draped in a national flag, was brought to the Minar from the BIRDEM morgue. A smartly turned out contingent of police led by deputy commissioner Syed Muktar Ahmed saluted the Liberation War leader. A stately guard of honour was accompanied by buglers. Family members and close relatives were present at the Minar throughout the ceremony. Awami League's Amir Hossain Amu and Tofail Ahmed, BNP's MK Anwar, CPB's Manjurul Ahsan Bulbul, Workers Party leader Rashed Khan Menon, JSD's Hasanul Huq Inu were among those paying last respects to a fellow political veteran. Professionals, intellectuals and representatives of various cultural organisations offered flowers paying their last respects to the people's leader. Manik, aged 69, died of lung cancer Monday morning at Comfort Hospital. bdnews24.com/s
